    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>You view time milliseconds ahead of reality, allowing you to avoid having your spells disrupted. When you’re casting a spell and you take damage or are subjected to an effect that could break your concentration and cause the spell to fail, you can spend 1 Resolve Point to move your body a fraction of an inch away from the part of the blow that would’ve disrupted you. Your spell doesn’t fail unless the damage or effect knocks you unconscious.</p>\n<p>In addition, you gain a +1 insight bonus to initiative that increases by 1 at level 12 and again at level 18.</p>"
